The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bomb in bus to Calcutta 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bomb in bus to Calcutta 
                            
	Gaya, May 14 (PTI): A country-made can-bomb was found by police, under the seat of a Calcutta-bound private bus in Gaya today, Bihar police said.        
	The bomb weighing about 2kg, planted under the seat, was found after the Banke Bazaar police received a tip-off, sources said.         
	The vehicle was a Kothi to Calcutta bus. Additional director-general of police (law and order) Anil Sinha said the bomb was crude and did not have a timer.        
	Mishap deaths        
	Two members of a wedding party were killed last night and six others were critically injured when a minibus fell into a ditch near Pipra village under Gadhani police station in Bihars Bhojpur district.         
	The accident occurred when the bus driver lost control while negotiating a bend and plunged into the ditch. Two persons identified as Ramashankar Singh and Ravinandan Sah died on the spot. The injured have been admitted to the Udvantnagar Government Hospital. Their condition is stated to be critical.                                                                                                                                                                         
